00006 /* Helper function that safely sprintfs to a buffer, allocation the buffer as needed. Note that the buffer is never freed (so
00007  * we don't have to allocate/free each time in, but that the conversion to std::string copies it. */
00008 static std::string
00009 str_printf(const char *fmt, ...)
00010 {
00011     va_list ap;
00012     static size_t bufsz = 128;
00013     static char *buf = new char[bufsz];
00014     va_start(ap, fmt);
00015 
00016     size_t need;
00017     while ((need=vsnprintf(buf, bufsz, fmt, ap))>bufsz) {
00018         delete[] buf;
00019         bufsz = need+1;
00020         buf = new char[bufsz];
00021     }
00022     va_end(ap);
00023     return buf;
00024 }

00032 void
00033 SgAsmExecutableFileFormat::hexdump(std::ostream &f, rose_addr_t base_addr, const unsigned char *data,
00034                                    size_t n, const HexdumpFormat &fmt)
00035 {
00036     /* Provide default formats. This is done here so that the header file doesn't depend on <inttypes.h> */
00037     const char *addr_fmt = fmt.addr_fmt ? fmt.addr_fmt : "0x%08"PRIx64": ";
00038     const char *numeric_fmt = fmt.numeric_fmt ? fmt.numeric_fmt : "%02x";
00039     const char *numeric_sep = fmt.numeric_sep ? fmt.numeric_sep : " ";
00040     const char *prefix = fmt.prefix ? fmt.prefix : "";
00041 
00042     char s[1024];
00043     sprintf(s, numeric_fmt, 0u);
00044     int numeric_width = strlen(s);
00045 
00046     if (fmt.multiline)
00047         f <<prefix;
00048 
00049     for (size_t i=0; i<n; i+=fmt.width) {
00050         /* Prefix and/or address */
00051         if (i>0)
00052             f <<"\n" <<prefix;
00053         f <<str_printf(addr_fmt, base_addr+i);
00054 
00055         /* Numeric byte values */
00056         if (fmt.show_numeric) {
00057             for (size_t j=0; j<fmt.width; j++) {
00058                 if (i+j<n) {
00059                     if (j>0)
00060                         f <<numeric_sep;
00061                     if (j>0 && 0 == j % fmt.colsize)
00062                         f <<" ";
00063                     f <<str_printf(numeric_fmt, data[i+j]);
00064                 } else if (fmt.pad_numeric) {
00065                     if (j>0)
00066                         f <<numeric_sep;
00067                     if (j>0 && 0 == j % fmt.colsize)
00068                         f <<" ";
00069                     f <<str_printf("%*s", numeric_width, "");
00070                 }
00071             }
00072         }
00073 
00074         if (fmt.show_numeric && fmt.show_chars)
00075             f <<" |";
00076         
00077         /* Character byte values */
00078         if (fmt.show_chars) {
00079             for (size_t j=0; j<fmt.width; j++) {
00080                 if (i+j>=n) {
00081                     if (fmt.pad_chars)
00082                         f <<" ";
00083                 } else if (isprint(data[i+j])) {
00084                     f <<data[i+j];
00085                 } else {
00086                     f <<".";
00087                 }
00088             }
00089             f <<"|";
00090         }
00091     }
00092 
00093     if (fmt.multiline)
00094         f <<"\n";
00095 }
